gomodel:SYNGO_2555  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Electron micrographs demonstrating the subcellular localization of m2 receptor protein\"\n- \" Electron micrograph of a rare somatic synapse between an unlabeled axon terminal (a) and an m2-immunoreactive neuron (~2). Reaction product is not present postsynaptically but is plentiful outside the region of this synapse (arrows).\"\n- \"D, Junctional complex (arrow) binding two m2-immunoreactive dendrites. The junctional densities appear intensely immunoreactive.\"\n- \"F, m2-positive axon terminal (a) and preterminal axon (arrow). Synaptic vesicles appear to be surrounded by reaction product.\"\n\n- A junctional complex is not a synapse.\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Twelve young adult male Sprague-Dawley (Harlan) rats were deeply anesthetized ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2555" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

